{
  "stem": "7598.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father helped whenever he-- when he could.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The German Jewish people, of course.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there weren't any organized-- charitable organizations at the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And presumably, as the German Jews did when they came here, they took job as au pairs or anything in order to survive.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my father, whom I rather worshiped and who was an intelligent man, had blinkers as far as that was concerned.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He was very aware of what was going on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Being in the diamond business, he would have had the opportunity of leaving, of going to America and always spoke about tomorrow, next week, next month, but we never did.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When the war broke out in September '39 between Great Britain and Germany, when Poland was invaded, it was then too late for my parents to try and get-- suddenly get to England.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I say that because people in the diamond trade found it easier to move than people who had factories or other things, which is why there are quite a number of Jews in the jewelry and in the diamond business, because you could take whatever little fortune you had in your hand and just get away.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I think it is because we were the diamond business I'm here to tell-- alive and here to tell the story.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that was-- yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was afterwards.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] From September 1939 to May 1940 when Germany invaded Benelux [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we still led a very comfortable life [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and somehow thought, although we knew that Belgium was engaged in the First World War, that perhaps the Germans wouldn't get any further.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They wouldn't get to France.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
